item.dc:creator: @sdouble sdouble
item.description:
@sdouble wrote:

Oh, you posted in the section for writing script, not using them. This confuses people when they are trying to help. Especially when you simply post “How can i get it to auto attack chickens ?” We don’t know if you posted in the right place and you want to write a chicken killing script, or you posted in the wrong place and just want to use a script someone else already wrote. Please be a little more careful with your posting. I got all excited about helping someone work on their script and was shot down because that’s not what you wanted.

item.description:
@Iamadam wrote:

Lol ok i spose u gotta start somewhere. When you have downloaded the file, the command to start it is ‘\CK()’
If you are using the normal chickens script, the command is
\chickens(Attack\Strength\Defence)
so if you wanted it to train your Defence, you’d write
\chickens(Defence)
